	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=223468"><span id=" ">Tennis</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">7 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I don't understand these posts that cry about selling these books for 75k and whatnot.&nbsp;&nbsp;Do you guys have any understanding of rudimentary economics?  Obviously, if they are priced that high, someone is willing to pay that much.  In fact, in all truth, the seller has virtually no control of the price of the item.  If he knows that the buying power of the market is willing to pay 75k, then it isn't greed that is making him price out at that level, it's common sense.  Don't hate because you can't afford.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
